{The 4\C and 4\H bids were control-showing. North is to play 6\D. East leads the \CJ.

Losers:   \S=2  \H=0  \D=2  \C=0  Total = 4

That loser count may be technically correct but actually it's wonky. As long as \Ds split 3-2 like they should you only have 1 loser in the suit. And if West has the \DQ you can finesse and have no losers. Also, those 2 \S losers could be ruffed in dummy.

Suppose you tried it like this: Win the \C, play \DA, then a \D to the \DJ, then pull the last trump with your \DK. That would only leave one trump in dummy for ruffing \S losers, but you could make the slam.

But suppose the \D finesse lost to East. And further suppose that East then played another \D. Since only 1 \S could be ruffed you'd be down 1. Try something else. 

Win the \C. Play the \DA and \DK, forgetting about even trying the finesse. If the \DQ falls that's good, but if it doesn't, no problem, just leave it out there. Then start on your other high cards. Take 2 more \Cs, 2 \Ss, and 2 \Hs. Then start cross-ruffing the last 4 \Ss and \Hs. The \DQ guy can trump in whenever he likes but you will make 12 tricks.

This is the complete deal. 

again to see what would have happened if you had finessed in trumps. 

Suppose you had won the first \C, then played \DA and lost the \D finesse to East's \DQ. East might have then played his last trump back to your \DJ and the hands would look like this.

You need the rest of the tricks but the best you can do now is to take the two high \Cs, the two high \Hs, the two high \Ss, one \H ruff in your hand and one \S ruff in dummy. Letting East pull that third round of trumps did you in.

This is how it would have looked if you had won the first \C trick, then just played the \DA and \DK, not trying the trump finesse. 

Leaving the master trump out, you would now proceed to take your two high \Cs, two high \Hs and two high \Ss.

Needing just three more tricks, and with two trumps in each hand you just cross-ruff \Hs and \S. East can ruff in with the \DQ at some point but he cannot prevent you from winning at least three of your trumps separately.}
[Play "W"]CJ

